      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JOCK FROM IBROX (3) was well supported last time and rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional, going on to clock 29.55 in a 7 length win at this track over 515m. Recorded the quickest time on the card last start. In great form and can continue his winning ways. KALANI CRUISE (1) has been out of the placings last two but shapes well for this if she can recapture her slick win a few runs back, getting around Wentworth Park over 520m in 29.88. Top win three back and can measure up again. OUR GIRL SASSY (2) resumed from a break finishing fourth (22.72) at Gosford in a Grade 5. Will be much improved and the longer journey suits. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. SHINING GIRL (7) can run a bold race on best form.",
